<h2>Register</h2>
{{#if message}}
<div class="error">{{ message }}</div>
{{/if}}
<form action="/register" method="post">
		<div class="form-group">
				<label>Email</label>
				<input type="text" class="form-control" name="email">
		</div>
		<div class="form-group">
				<label>Password</label>
				<input type="password" class="form-control" name="password">
		</div>

		<button type="submit" class="btn btn-warning btn-lg">Register</button>
</form>

<hr>

<p><a href="/">Login</a></p>


<p>(4/27/18) Known Bug: Please do not register an email with a '.' (period) character, as it causes issues with database updates. A fix might come after the deadline, but deploying the website is the priority</p>
